title: Camel - Camel
description:
Camel is the first studio album by English progressive rock band Camel. It was released in 1973. The bonus track Homage To The God Of Light was originally released in Peter Bardens's solo album The Answer in 1970.
   The record was not a success and the band moved to the Deram Records division of Decca Records (UK).

In 1974 they released their second album; the critically acclaimed Mirage, on which Latimer showed he was also adept on flute. Although failing to chart at home, it gained success on the U.S. west coast, prompting a three-month tour there.
